<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,152,1079]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,872,899]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was first described based on specimens from Arabica coffee infested with the white stem borer, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat. The" authorityName="Chevrolat. The" box="[281,704,908,934]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xylotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripes">
<emphasis box="[281,532,908,934]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Xylotrechus quadripes</emphasis>
Chevrolat. The
</taxonomicName>
male of this species is promptly recognized by having the clypeus rounded; the notaulus complete; the metapostnotum irregularly foveolate; the hypopygium with a long plate, with a flap and the posterior margin almost straight.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,152,1079]" box="[199,1256,1016,1043]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1017,1043]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</emphasis>
The illustrations of the body, genitalia and hypopygium were done using 
<typeStatus box="[1141,1252,1017,1043]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
